hands_on_practices.problem:
Let $G$ be a finite group of order $|G| = 1372$. For a prime $p$, a Sylow $p$-subgroup of $G$ is a subgroup whose order is the highest power of $p$ that divides the order of $G$. The first Sylow theorem guarantees the existence of such subgroups for every prime dividing $|G|$.

Which of the following options correctly lists the orders of the Sylow $p$-subgroups of $G$ for all relevant prime factors $p$?

A. {2, 7}

B. {4, 49}

C. {2, 343}

D. {4, 343}

E. {1, 4, 343}
